India Equity Movers: Gammon, Glenmark, Madras Fertilizers

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-05-16T11:02:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/india-equity-movers-gammon-glenmark-madras-fertilizers.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the 3:30 p.m. close in Mumbai.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, fell
186.25, or 1 percent, to 18,345.03. The BSE 200 Index decreased
0.9 percent to 2,273.35.  Gammon Infrastructure Projects Ltd. (GISP)   rose 4.8
percent to 18.45 rupees, the biggest advance in more than a
month. The company will consider on May 19 a proposal to sell
shares to existing holders, it said in a statement May 13.  Glenmark Pharmaceuticals Ltd. (GNP)   surged 12 percent to
306.1 rupees, the highest in more than three months. The
drugmaker’s unit signed an agreement granting France’s Sanofi a
license to develop a monoclonal antibody GBR 500, according to
an exchange filing today.  Hindustan Zinc Ltd. (HZ)   declined 1.4 percent to 129.2
rupees, the lowest since March 22. India’s largest producer cut
lead prices by 1.9 percent to 123,300 rupees a metric ton
starting today, according to the company’s website.  Kirloskar Brothers Ltd. (KKB)   gained 2.7 percent to 156
rupees, its steepest climb since May 6. The Indian maker of
 machine tools  agreed to sell unit Gondwana Engineers Ltd. to
Doshion Veolia Water Solutions Pvt., a subsidiary of Doshion
Ltd., for 474.4 million rupees ($10.5 million), according to a
May 14 exchange filing.  Madras Fertilizers Ltd. (MDF)   surged 9.6 percent to
28.65 rupees, the steepest advance since April 4. India’s
fertilizer ministry is considering a plan to help revive the
state-run company by writing off 5.5 billion rupees of loans,
the  Press Trust of India  reported, citing an official it didn’t
identify.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ameya Karve in Mumbai at 
 akarve@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
